-- Africa's Growth Led By Policies, Not Commodity Demand, AFDB President Says
-- B y   E m i l y   B o w e r s
-- 2010-10-27T08:58:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/africa-s-growth-led-by-policies-not-commodites-afdb-s-kaberuka-says.html
Africa’s economic growth has been
led by changes in governance policies across the continent over
the past decade, rather than demand for its commodities, African
Development Bank President Donald Kaberuka said.  “There is strong reason to be bullish” on prospects for
future growth, Kaberuka told a conference in Gammarth, Tunisia,
today. Africans need to be “pragmatically realistic about the
potential setbacks,” he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emily Bowers at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net  